# nextoffice — Project Context

> Full architecture details are in @CLAUDE.md — read it before making any change.

## Stack
- **API**: NestJS (port 3000) — `apps/api/`
- **Web**: Next.js 16 (port 3001) — `apps/web/`
- **DB**: MariaDB via Prisma v7 + `@prisma/adapter-mariadb`
- **Queue**: Bull/Redis — four queues: `line-events`, `file-intake`, `ai-processing`, `outbound-messages`
- **Storage**: MinIO (bucket `nextoffice`)

## Critical Rules

### BigInt IDs
All Prisma `@id` fields are `BigInt`. Always call `serialize()` before returning from any service/controller. Never let a BigInt reach JSON serialization.

### Prisma Client Location
Generated at `apps/api/generated/prisma` — **not** the default path. Import from there.

### LLM Calls
Use `axios.post` to `https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages` directly — not the Anthropic SDK. See `ClassifierService` or `ReasoningService` for the pattern.

### TypeScript Strictness
- `apps/api`: `noImplicitAny: false`, `strictNullChecks: false` — loose on purpose
- `apps/web`: `strict: true` — enforce types

### Next.js 16
Before editing `apps/web/`, read `apps/web/AGENTS.md`. APIs differ from training data.

## Prisma CLI (run from `apps/api/`)
```bash
npx prisma generate    # after schema changes
npx prisma db push     # sync schema → DB
```

## Working with Claude Code
- Claude Code runs in the Cursor terminal — they share the same filesystem
- Claude Code handles: shell commands, git, long refactors, multi-file tasks
- Cursor handles: inline edits, quick fixes, screenshot error analysis
- **Do not edit the same file simultaneously** — always check Claude Code is idle before making inline edits
- `CLAUDE.md` is the shared context — keep it up to date when architecture changes
